The paper deals with distributed consensus, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). It also involves strategic manipulations by rational agents, which falls under game theory (cs.GT) and collusion-resistant protocols (cs.CR). The use of deterministic and randomized protocols involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), and the consideration of synchronous systems falls under control systems (cs.SY).
